import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['US_Gross'], data['Worldwide_Gross'])
    plt.xlabel('US_Gross')
    plt.ylabel('Worldwide_Gross')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of US_Gross and Worldwide_Gross?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

    return plt;

chart.show()

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data_to_plot = [data['Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating'], data['IMDB_Rating']]
    plt.boxplot(data_to_plot, labels=['Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating', 'IMDB_Rating'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating and IMDB_Rating?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.hist(data['Running_Time_min'], bins=20, edgecolor='black')

    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Running_Time_min?', wrap=True)

    return plt;

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    mpaa_genre_counts = data.groupby(['MPAA_Rating', 'Major_Genre']).size().unstack()
    mpaa_genre_counts.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
    
    plt.title("What is the distribution of MPAA_Rating and Major_Genre?", wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
